Author Information
Enrique R. Arzac is Professor of Finance and Economics at the Columbia University Graduate School of Business, Director of the Merger, Buyouts, and Restructuring program for executives at Columbia Business School, and Co-Director of the Merger and Acquisitions program for executives at London Business School. He is the author of many academic articles in financial economics and has been consultant to corporations and financial institutions in North and South America and Europe. He is a director of the Adams Express Company, Petroleum and Resources Corporation and Credit Suisse Asset Management funds.


See More
See Less



New To This Edition


Introductory material added to make content more
readable and appealing to a wider audience
Addition of real-life examples and illustrations based
upon recent transactions. In particular, on mergers and
acquisitions, deal-making, leveraged buyouts, and
restructuring.
Updated content in reference to recent academic research
and its implication for applied valuation.



See More
See Less



The Wiley Advantage
Detailed treatment of free cash flow valuation provides students with methods for dealing with complex yet all-too-common valuation problems.

Extensive discussion of financing and valuation of leverage buyouts (LBOs) provides a useful reference for professional practice.

Unique coverage of valuation of special offer structures (prices guarantees and collars) as well as contract design resolves differences of opinion in valuations and mergers and acquisitions.

Covers recapitalization of troubled companies and restructuring decisions, including tax and accounting issues.

Valuation Aids CD: The text includes software that allows students to perform specialized calculations, including estimating the equity premium and valuing financial and real options.

DealModeler CD-ROM with User s Manual: This optional comprehensive financial modeling Excel workbook can generate various financial statements and perform the valuation of mergers, acquisitions, etc.




